<br>
For the people who for some reason thought he was actually arguing the points about Manaburn, on behalf of the wizards of EQ (who are all represented by the voices in my head):<br>
<br>
1) Yes, Manaburn was pretty damn powerful.<br>
<br>
2) No, that did not mean TMB kills were trivial, although they could be fairly easy if everything goes right (much like any raid, really).<br>
<br>
3) The lack of triviality has to do, in part, with shitty coding by VI. Talking about the theory and ignoring the practice in this regard is pretty pointless.<br>
<br>
4) No, most wizards with MB did not spend their time farming Kunark content. They had better things to do.<br>
<br>
5) No, most of the Kunark content on Vazaelle did not fall to TMB. Asserting this is just another way of saying you're slow and disorganized. Stuff that you don't see up was ganked by someone. Even at its peak, Vazaelle only had two handfuls of wizards with MB, most of them playing at Euro/US times.<br>
<br>
6) Yes, MB wouldn't work as-was in PoP. Either it needed to be disabled in PoP (my preference) or retuned (what we got).<br>
<br>
7) Yes, pre-nerf MB had utility on raids where fast kills were important (Trakanon, Zlandicar, anyone who cycles DTs, et cetera).<br>
<br>
8) Yes, due to its 1 point of aggro (much like archery has diminished aggro for its damage), it could also be used in long Luclin fights where the wizard had time and mod rods to mod to full before they'd normally begin with their normal aggro-producing nuking chores.<br>
<br>
9) No, the nerfed MB is not useful in either of these circumstances. It was always very mana-inefficient, and now it's more so, with a hard cap of just over 9000 points of damage for a full burn. Considering even with my very average manapool, I can do more than 20k of damage with my full manapool, this is hardly some exceptional value, especially considering wizards' other tools for dealing with highly resistant opponents.<br>
<br>
10) Yes, the Kunark spawns are easy and people one group (or less) them before, during and after the MB era without MB wizards.<br>
<br>
11) Yes, this content is still prime material to many folks.<br>
<br>
12) Yes, they should probably have more parity between the classes and make spawned versions of Gorenaire, Venril Sathir and Servilious, just like they do Ragefire, Trakanon, Venril Sathir's Remains and Faydedar.<br>
<br>
13) No, wizards have never denied any of this. There's never been a giant conspiracy about MB -- in fact, on a stickied thread at Graffe's for two weeks before Luclin came out, people hashed out how this could work, picked targets, and as the targets were knocked down, posted full info usually within the hour the kill occurred. None of this has ever been done under a veil of secrecy and none of it has ever been denied to be happening.<br>
<br>
14) Yes, we have denied that these kills went from demonstration/stunt kills (see Sontalak) to an ongoing, and cockblocking, farming session. This is because it didn't happen.<br>
<br>
15) Yes, people claim it did. Asking them to provide proof, even such insubstantial and fakeable proof as rants on a server's R&amp;F boards -- where things like the mythical pre-change Ragefire ganks would almost certainly appear, especially if they were taking place in large numbers -- results in insults and declarations about how proof isn't needed, because it's &quot;clearly&quot; true.<br>
<br>
16) No, it's not clearly true. Put up or shut up.<br>
<br>
17) Yes, Verant said point-blank in multiple Fan Faires that they saw no problem with Manaburn and had no intention at the time of changing anything. This is well into the MB era, when the urban myths of &quot;my best friend's server&quot; being held hostage by rampaging MB wizards were popular.<br>
<br>
18) Yes, they either changed their mind or lied. They do both.<br>
<br>
19) Yes, this exact same cycle is beginning again with other classes. Instead of bitching about it, figuring out what's important (letting lower level folk farm their own epic pieces, probably) and making the needed changes (more spawned versions of these jokers) is a better solution than the same stupid cycle of hysteria and nerfing, with nothing really changing in the end.<br>
<br>
20) No, no more paladin, warrior, bard or even wizard epics showed up on Vazaelle after the nerf. These spawns left the game at about the same rate as during the MB era, maybe a little slower.<br>
<br>
21) Yes, this has gone on too long, and I'll STFU in a moment.<br>
<br>
22) Yes, Team IHT, I need Disintegrate and Winds of Gelid. Let me know if they drop and you're not asking an insane crackhead price for either (20k is insane crackhead territory for either, btw).<br>
<br>
OK, bring back the picture of the dead horse, please. I'm out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=owwiefixer@vazaellecommunitycenter>Owwiefixer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/19/02 7:29:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3503.topic&index=123>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noobs</span><hr size=1> bigemnose-<br>
